    {
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
      "name": "Rejuvenation",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>As a manifestation of death incarnate, a danse macabre is not itself subject to permanent destruction. If reduced to 0 hit points, it vanishes, only to rejuvenate at full hit points in [[/br 1d4 #days]]{1d4 days}. Only by destroying the creature and then performing the consecrate ritual on the site it manifested upon prevents the undead monster's reappearance.</p>"
        },
